  <summary>Linux Bluetooth proximity lock</summary>
  <description>
    <p>
      BlueLatch locks an Ubuntu GNOME session when a trusted Bluetooth phone is no longer nearby.
      It never auto-unlocks the system and suppresses repeated re-locking after a manual unlock until the phone returns.
    </p>
  </description>
